-- FRAME 1: evaluate draft-dsl (soft cell, LLM) — ⊢∘ ITERATION 1
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- Ready set: { draft-dsl }
-- ⊢∘ refine begins: draft-dsl is the target cell, iteration 1.
-- v0.2: oracles on draft-dsl are aspirational (⊢∘-managed).

⊢ draft-dsl
  given domain→name ≡ "RecipeCell"
  given domain→requirements ≡ [...]
  yield grammar, explanation

  ∴ Design a mini-DSL called «domain→name» for cooking recipes...

-- LLM evaluation:

  yield grammar ≡ "
    <recipe>       ::= RECIPE <name> SERVES <n> TIME <duration>
                         <ingredients> <steps>
    <ingredients>  ::= INGREDIENTS: <ingredient>+
    <ingredient>   ::= <name> <amount> <unit> [OR <name> <amount> <unit> RATIO <ratio>]
    <steps>        ::= STEPS: <step>+
    <step>         ::= <label>: <action> FOR <duration>
                      | <label>: <action> FOR <duration> THEN <label>
                      | <label>: <action> FOR <duration> WHILE <label>
                      | <label>: WAIT-UNTIL <label> REMAINING <duration>
                      | IF-SUB <ingredient-name> : <action> FOR <duration>
    <duration>     ::= <n> min | <n> hr
    <ratio>        ::= <n>:<n>
    <amount>       ::= <number> [<fraction>]
    <unit>         ::= cups | tbsp | tsp | oz | g | lb | cloves | whole
  "

  yield explanation ≡ "RecipeCell grammar walkthrough:

    RECIPE header: Every recipe starts with RECIPE followed by its name,
    serving count (SERVES n), and estimated total time (TIME duration).

    INGREDIENTS block: Lists each ingredient with amount and unit.
    Substitutions use OR: 'butter 2 tbsp OR olive-oil 2 tbsp RATIO 1:1'
    means you can replace butter with olive oil at equal quantity.

    STEPS block: Each step has a label, an action description, and a duration.
    Timing operators:
    - THEN: sequential — step B starts after step A finishes.
    - WHILE: parallel — step B runs concurrently with step A.
    - WAIT-UNTIL ... REMAINING: start this step when another step has
      the specified time remaining (e.g., WAIT-UNTIL rice REMAINING 5 min).

    IF-SUB: Conditional step tied to a substitution choice. Only executes
    if the named ingredient substitution is active.

    Durations use 'min' or 'hr'. Amounts support fractions (1/2, 1/4)."

-- oracle checks (aspirational under ⊢∘):
--   ⊨ grammar defines syntax for: recipe, ingredient, step, timing, substitution → ✓
--   ⊨ grammar includes at least one timing operator → ✓ (THEN, WHILE, WAIT-UNTIL)
--   ⊨ grammar includes substitution syntax with ratio adjustment → ✓ (OR...RATIO)
--   ⊨ explanation covers every production rule in grammar → ✓
--   NOTE: All pass on first draft. Aspirational oracles serve as feedback
--   signals — even if they failed, ⊢∘ would continue (not block freezing).

