-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- FRAME 7: evaluate redesign (soft cell, LLM) — ⊢∘ ITERATION 1
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- Ready set: { redesign }
-- Guard: critique→is-clean = false → PASS (redesign fires)

⊢ redesign
  given draft-dsl→grammar ≡ "<recipe> ::= RECIPE <name> SERVES <n> TIME <duration>..."
  given draft-dsl→explanation ≡ "RecipeCell grammar walkthrough:..."
  given critique→awkward-parts ≡ ["A1: THEN+WHILE ambiguity...", "A2: multiple timing ops...",
    "A3: IF-SUB no timing...", "A4: mixed-unit ratio...", "A5: THEN reads backwards..."]
  given critique→is-clean ≡ false
  given domain→requirements ≡ [...]
  yield grammar', explanation'

  ∴ Redesign the grammar to fix every awkward part...

-- LLM evaluation:

  yield grammar' ≡ "
    <recipe>       ::= RECIPE <name> SERVES <n> TIME <duration>
                         <ingredients> <steps>
    <ingredients>  ::= INGREDIENTS: <ingredient>+
    <ingredient>   ::= <name> <amount> <unit> [OR <name> <amount> <unit>]
    <steps>        ::= STEPS: <step>+
    <step>         ::= <label>: <action> FOR <duration> [<timing>]
                      | IF-SUB <ingredient-name> : <action> FOR <duration> [<timing>]
    <timing>       ::= AFTER <label>
                      | ALONGSIDE <label>
                      | STARTS-WHEN <label> HAS <duration> LEFT
    <duration>     ::= <n> min | <n> hr
    <amount>       ::= <number> [<fraction>]
    <unit>         ::= cups | tbsp | tsp | oz | g | lb | cloves | whole
  "

  yield explanation' ≡ "RecipeCell v2 grammar walkthrough:

    Changes from v1:
    - REMOVED RATIO: substitutions are now always same-unit. If you write
      'butter 2 tbsp OR olive-oil 2 tbsp', the amounts are explicit per
      ingredient. No ambiguous cross-unit ratios. (fixes A4)
    - RENAMED THEN → AFTER: 'scramble FOR 4 min AFTER heat' reads
      naturally as 'scramble happens after heat finishes.' (fixes A5)
    - RENAMED WHILE → ALONGSIDE: 'prep-veg FOR 8 min ALONGSIDE rice'
      reads as 'prep vegetables at the same time as rice.' (fixes A1)
    - ONE TIMING PER STEP: each step may carry at most one timing clause.
      No chaining AFTER+ALONGSIDE. The old 'THEN saute WHILE cook-pasta'
      becomes two steps: 'simmer-sauce AFTER saute' and a separate note
      that simmer-sauce and cook-pasta overlap via ALONGSIDE. (fixes A1, A2)
    - STARTS-WHEN: replaces WAIT-UNTIL...REMAINING. 'heat-wok STARTS-WHEN
      rice HAS 5 min LEFT' is clearer. (fixes A2)
    - IF-SUB GETS TIMING: conditional steps can now carry a timing clause
      just like regular steps. 'IF-SUB tofu: press tofu FOR 15 min AFTER rice'
      is valid. Conditional steps without timing run before the first
      timed step (prep phase). (fixes A3)

    Preserved from v1:
    - RECIPE header (name, servings, total-time) unchanged.
    - INGREDIENTS block with OR for substitutions.
    - STEPS block with labels and durations.
    - Readable to a home cook — all keywords are English words."

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ grammar' addresses every awkward part with severity ≥ 3
--     → ✓ (A1: AFTER/ALONGSIDE split; A2: one-timing-per-step + STARTS-WHEN;
--           A3: IF-SUB with timing)
--   ⊨ grammar' still satisfies all domain→requirements → ✓
--     (recipes ✓, timing ✓, substitutions ✓, conditionals ✓, readability ✓)
--   ⊨ §redesign has same given/yield signature as «§draft-dsl» → ✓
--     (both yield grammar, explanation)

