-- SPAWNED CELL: example-1 (v2)
⊢ example-1
  yield code, label

  ⊢= label ← "medium"
  ⊢= code ← "RECIPE Pasta with Tomato Sauce SERVES 4 TIME 35 min

    INGREDIENTS:
      pasta 400 g
      fresh-tomatoes 800 g OR canned-tomatoes 800 g
      garlic 3 cloves
      olive-oil 2 tbsp
      parmesan 50 g OR nutritional-yeast 30 g
      basil 10 g
      salt 1 tsp

    STEPS:
      boil-water: bring water to boil FOR 10 min
      cook-pasta: add pasta to boiling water FOR 12 min AFTER boil-water
      saute: heat olive-oil and garlic FOR 3 min
      simmer-sauce: add tomatoes and simmer FOR 20 min AFTER saute
      drain: drain pasta FOR 1 min AFTER cook-pasta
      combine: toss pasta with sauce FOR 2 min AFTER drain
      garnish: add parmesan and basil FOR 1 min AFTER combine
  "

-- NOTE: simmer-sauce and cook-pasta no longer chained with ambiguous
-- THEN+WHILE. simmer-sauce AFTER saute runs independently. cook-pasta
-- AFTER boil-water runs independently. The two tracks naturally overlap
-- because neither has a timing dep on the other. Parallelism is implicit
-- when steps don't reference each other — cleaner than explicit WHILE.

