-- Ready set: { redesign }
-- Issues are all severity ≤ 2 (none ≥ 3). The grammar is nearly clean.
-- Redesign will make minor polish passes.

⊢ redesign
  given draft-dsl→grammar ≡ "<recipe> ::= ... [v2]"
  given draft-dsl→explanation ≡ "RecipeCell v2 grammar walkthrough:..."
  given critique→awkward-parts ≡ ["B1: implicit parallelism unclear...",
    "B2: no RATIO acceptable...", "B3: IF-SUB name matching undefined..."]
  given critique→is-clean ≡ false
  given domain→requirements ≡ [...]
  yield grammar', explanation'

  ∴ Redesign the grammar to fix every awkward part...

-- LLM evaluation:

  yield grammar' ≡ "
    <recipe>       ::= RECIPE <name> SERVES <n> TIME <duration>
                         <ingredients> <steps>
    <ingredients>  ::= INGREDIENTS: <ingredient>+
    <ingredient>   ::= <name> <amount> <unit> [OR <name> <amount> <unit>]
    <steps>        ::= STEPS: <step>+
    <step>         ::= <label>: <action> FOR <duration> [<timing>]
                      | IF-SUB <ingredient-name> : <action> FOR <duration> [<timing>]
                      | NOTE: <text>
    <timing>       ::= AFTER <label>
                      | ALONGSIDE <label>
                      | STARTS-WHEN <label> HAS <duration> LEFT
    <duration>     ::= <n> min | <n> hr
    <amount>       ::= <number> [<fraction>]
    <unit>         ::= cups | tbsp | tsp | oz | g | lb | cloves | whole
    <ingredient-name> ::= -- matches exactly the <name> in an OR clause
  "

  yield explanation' ≡ "RecipeCell v3 grammar walkthrough:

    Changes from v2:
    - ADDED NOTE: A free-text annotation line in the steps block. Used to
      document implicit parallelism: 'NOTE: simmer-sauce and cook-pasta
      run in parallel (no dependency between them).' (fixes B1)
    - CLARIFIED IF-SUB matching: <ingredient-name> in IF-SUB must match
      exactly the <name> token from an OR clause in the ingredients block.
      'IF-SUB tofu' matches 'chicken 500 g OR tofu 400 g' because 'tofu'
      appears as the substitution name. 'IF-SUB firm-tofu' would NOT match
      unless the ingredient is listed as 'firm-tofu'. (fixes B3)
    - B2 (RATIO removal) accepted as a good trade-off. No change needed.

    All v2 constructs preserved:
    - AFTER, ALONGSIDE, STARTS-WHEN timing operators
    - One timing operator per step
    - IF-SUB with optional timing clause
    - RECIPE header, INGREDIENTS block, STEPS block"

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ grammar' addresses every awkward part with severity ≥ 3 → ✓ (vacuous —
--     no severity ≥ 3 issues in this round; all were ≤ 2)
--   ⊨ grammar' still satisfies all domain→requirements → ✓
--   ⊨ §redesign has same given/yield signature as «§draft-dsl» → ✓

